"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921904","Treasury","false","2018-06-19","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) is responsible for the collection and publication of data on UK imports and exports of goods to and from the UK. HMRC releases this information monthly, as a National Statistic called the Overseas Trade in Goods Statistics.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC is unable to provide information regarding the re-export of fur. It does not collect data that would identify fur being re-exported for trade between the UK and other EU Member States. Following the application of statistical disclosure control HMRC is unable to provide the data for re-exports of fur to non-EU countries, as the information would identify a person or allow their identity to be deduced.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-06-19T13:57:15.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921904/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921904/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-11","Furs: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the value of fur re-exports to the UK's five largest destinations by value of such exports was in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","152041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921905","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-19","<p>My rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy has not offered or granted financial support to the international fur trade.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-06-19T13:24:37.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921905/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921905/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-11","Furs: Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what financial support his Department (a) offered and (b) granted to the international fur trade in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","152042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921906","Department for International Trade","false","2018-06-18","<p>Details of the meetings held by the Department for International Trade (DIT) Ministers are published on the Gov.UK website and can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-international-trade&amp;publication_type=transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-international-trade&amp;publication_type=transparency-data</a></p><p> </p><p>Below ministerial level, officials routinely meet trade representatives from a wide range of sectors with a diverse range of interests as part of general engagement activities of the department.</p><p> </p><p>No DIT Ministers have met directly with the International Fur Traders Association.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2018-06-18T13:42:01.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921906/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921906/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-06-11","Department for International Trade: International Fur Trade Federation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what meetings have taken place between Ministers or officials of his Department and representatives of the International Fur Traders Association since his Department was established to date.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","152043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921907","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-19","<p>Neither BEIS Ministers or officials have met with representatives of the International Fur Federation.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-06-19T13:24:20.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921907/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921907/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-11","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: International Fur Trade Federation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what meetings have taken place between Ministers or officials of his Department and representatives of the International Fur Traders Association from 2010 to date.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","152044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921908","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-20","<p>Our records do not show any meetings between Defra Ministers or officials and the International Fur Traders Association from 2010 to date.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-20T17:06:59.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921908/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921908/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-11","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: International Fur Trade Federation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what meetings have taken place between Ministers or officials of his Department and representatives of the International Fur Traders Association from 2010 to date.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","152045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921909","Treasury","false","2018-06-19","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p><p> </p><p>Details of ministerial and Permanent Secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/senior-officials-expenses" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/senior-officials-expenses</a></p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-06-19T14:04:50.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921909/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921909/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-11","Treasury: International Fur Trade Federation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what meetings have taken place between Ministers or officials of his Department and representatives of the International Fur Traders Association from 2010 to date.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","152046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921910","Home Office","false","2018-06-22","<p>On 8 March we launched a 12 week public consultation on proposals for a landmark domestic abuse Bill and a supporting package of practical action to transform the response to domestic abuse. The consultation closed on 31 May. Over 3,200 responses to the consultation were received. The responses to the consultation are being considered and a draft Bill will be published later this session.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-06-22T11:31:15.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921910/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921910/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-11","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the timetable is for his Department to respond to its consultation on the draft Domestic Violence and Abuse Bill; and what the timetable is for further steps to be taken in relation to that Bill.","false","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","152117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921911","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Government is aware of the concerns amongst those living in park homes about the commission rate payable on sale. In our recent summary of responses to the Review of Park Homes legislation, issued last month, we agreed to give further consideration to this issue. My officials are currently collating the relevant evidence.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-06-18T14:36:43.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921911/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921911/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921911/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-11","Mobile Homes: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to reduce the commission rate payable on the sale of a park home.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","152280"
