"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921913","Home Office","false","2018-06-14","<p>On 8 March we launched a 12 week public consultation on proposals for a landmark domestic abuse Bill and a supporting package of practical action to transform the response to domestic abuse. The consultation closed on 31 May. Over 3,200 responses to the consultation were received. The responses to the consultation are being considered and a draft Bill will be published later this session.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-06-14T16:13:54.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921913/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921913/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-11","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the timetable is for his Department to respond to its consultation on the draft Domestic Violence and Abuse Bill; and what the timetable is for further steps to be taken in relation to that Bill.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","152274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921914","Home Office","false","2018-06-14","<p>On 8 March we launched a 12 week public consultation on proposals for a landmark domestic abuse Bill and a supporting package of practical action to transform the response to domestic abuse. The consultation closed on 31 May. Over 3,200 responses to the consultation were received. The responses to the consultation are being considered and a draft Bill will be published later this session.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-06-14T16:15:43.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921914/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921914/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-11","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the timetable is for his Department to respond to its consultation on the draft Domestic Violence and Abuse Bill; and what the timetable is for further steps to be taken in relation to that Bill.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","152216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921915","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-14","<p>As I indicated in my answer of 23 April 2018 to Question 135211, the review should cover the period from 25 June 2013 to 24 June 2018. It will therefore need to take into account the 5<sup>th</sup> annual report to Parliament on the use of closed material procedure under the Justice and Security Act 2013, which the Government aims to submit in the Autumn. A reviewer has not been appointed yet. Discussions between officials are ongoing and an announcement will be made in due course</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-06-14T16:24:26.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921915/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921915/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-11","Justice and Security Act 2013","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 23 April 2018 to Question 135211, whether a person has been appointed to conduct the review of the operation of sections 6 to 11 of the Justice and Security Act 2013; and when that review is scheduled to begin.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","152051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921916","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-14","<p>The total number of airport identification cards (“airside passes”) held by UK airports is in the region of 230,000. The Department for Transport does not hold information on the numbers of airport identification cards issued by financial year. The number of airport identification cards held at any one time or at any one airport is not static and may change on a daily basis. The issue and management of airport identification cards is a matter for each airport operator to handle in line with regulatory requirements outlined in the National Aviation Security Programme.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-06-14T08:17:29.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921916/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921916/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-11","Airports: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on the number of airside security passes issued for UK airports in each financial year from 2009-10 to 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","152052"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921917","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-14","<p>The total number of staff directly employed by HS2 Ltd in each of the last eight years is as follows:</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of Direct HS2 Staff</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010 - 2011</strong></p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011 - 2012</strong></p></td><td><p>42</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012 - 2013</strong></p></td><td><p>178</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013 - 2014</strong></p></td><td><p>380</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014 - 2015</strong></p></td><td><p>527</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015 - 2016</strong></p></td><td><p>918</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2016 - 2017</strong></p></td><td><p>1249</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2017 - 2018</strong></p></td><td><p>1346</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>These figures show the number that were employed in each financial year. It varies slightly from published figures contained in the Annual Report and Accounts and the Corporate Plan as this table only includes Employees, Graduates and Apprentices and is not net of people who have left in the Financial year.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-06-14T13:29:42.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921917/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921917/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-11","High Speed Two: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many staff worked for HS2 Ltd in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","152053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921918","Home Office","false","2018-06-14","<p>On 8 March we launched a 12 week public consultation on proposals for a landmark domestic abuse Bill and a supporting package of practical action to transform the response to domestic abuse. The consultation closed on 31 May. Over 3,200 responses to the consultation were received. The responses to the consultation are being considered and a draft Bill will be published later this session.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-06-14T16:17:23.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921918/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921918/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-11","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the timetable is for his Department to respond to it's consultation on the draft Domestic Violence and Abuse Bill; and what the timetable is for further steps to be taken in relation to that Bill.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","152298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921919","Home Office","false","2018-06-14","<p>On 8 March we launched a 12 week public consultation on proposals for a landmark domestic abuse Bill and a supporting package of practical action to transform the response to domestic abuse. The consultation closed on 31 May. Over 3,200 responses to the consultation were received. The responses to the consultation are being considered and a draft Bill will be published later this session.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-06-14T16:18:34.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921919/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921919/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-11","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the timetable is for his Department to respond to it's consultation on the draft Domestic Violence and Abuse Bill; and what the timetable is for further steps to be taken in relation to that Bill.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","152058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921920","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>DEFRA used publicly available data on waste disposal held by the Environment Agency to confirm that the Lakeside energy from waste plant is not a strategic asset and its loss would not affect the UK’s ability to meet environmental targets e.g. diversion from landfill. Therefore there is neither a statutory nor a policy reason to mandate replacement of the plant in the proposed Airports National Policy Statement.</p><p> </p><p>The Lakeside energy from waste High Temperature Incinerator (HTI) mainly treats clinical waste. In the South East and London Regions (which includes the Lakeside facility) there are three HTIs (including Lakeside) with permitted capacity of 68kt. However, in 2016 only 57kt of waste was treated in total at these facilities and 5kt (or 9% of the total capacity) at Lakeside. The clinical waste burned at Lakeside does not have to be dealt with by an HTI. There are six clinical waste plants in the South East and London Regions (including Lakeside) therefore the loss of the clinical waste tonnage at Lakeside could be met by other facilities.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","152119","2018-06-18T14:09:46.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921920/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921920/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921920/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-11","Lakeside Energy from Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to paragraph 1.113 of the Government Response to the Transport Committee Report on the revised draft Airports National Policy Statement, HC 548. what the evidential basis was for his Department's statement that there is sufficient waste management capacity to absorb any Lakeside loss.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","152118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921921","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>DEFRA used publicly available data on waste disposal held by the Environment Agency to confirm that the Lakeside energy from waste plant is not a strategic asset and its loss would not affect the UK’s ability to meet environmental targets e.g. diversion from landfill. Therefore there is neither a statutory nor a policy reason to mandate replacement of the plant in the proposed Airports National Policy Statement.</p><p> </p><p>The Lakeside energy from waste High Temperature Incinerator (HTI) mainly treats clinical waste. In the South East and London Regions (which includes the Lakeside facility) there are three HTIs (including Lakeside) with permitted capacity of 68kt. However, in 2016 only 57kt of waste was treated in total at these facilities and 5kt (or 9% of the total capacity) at Lakeside. The clinical waste burned at Lakeside does not have to be dealt with by an HTI. There are six clinical waste plants in the South East and London Regions (including Lakeside) therefore the loss of the clinical waste tonnage at Lakeside could be met by other facilities.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","152118","2018-06-18T14:09:46.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921921/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921921/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921921/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-11","Lakeside Energy from Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which waste disposal facilities with High Temperature Incinerators his Department has assessed as having enough spare capacity to deal with the loss of Lakeside Energy from Waste in the event of the construction of a third runway at Heathrow.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","152119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921922","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Appraisal of Sustainability, published alongside the proposed Airports National Policy Statement, identifies the potential soil contamination issues in relation to the Heathrow Northwest Runway scheme. The Airports Commission also included £123m, plus optimism bias, for site levelling and soil remediation within its cost and commercial assessment.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has been clear that expansion will be privately financed and costs will not fall on the taxpayer. This includes any land decontamination costs.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","152121","2018-06-18T14:04:00.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921922/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921922/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921922/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-11","Heathrow Airport: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has made an estimate of the total cost of decontaminating any necessary land before a third runway can be constructed at Heathrow.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","152120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921923","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Appraisal of Sustainability, published alongside the proposed Airports National Policy Statement, identifies the potential soil contamination issues in relation to the Heathrow Northwest Runway scheme. The Airports Commission also included £123m, plus optimism bias, for site levelling and soil remediation within its cost and commercial assessment.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has been clear that expansion will be privately financed and costs will not fall on the taxpayer. This includes any land decontamination costs.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","152120","2018-06-18T14:04:00.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921923/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921923/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921923/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-11","Heathrow Airport: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the taxpayer is planned to be liable for any proportion of the total cost of decontaminating land before a third runway can be constructed at Heathrow.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","152121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921924","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Secretary of State met with the Leader of the House on 27 March to discuss airport expansion and the revised draft Airports National Policy Statement. Any debate and vote must be held within the 21 sitting days of the proposed Airports National Policy Statement being laid in Parliament, with the last sitting day being 9 July. The Leader will announce business in the normal way.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-18T15:50:06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921924/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921924/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-11","Airports: National Policy Statements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has had discussions with the Leader of the House on how long the Airports National Policy Statement will be debated for.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","152122"
