"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921934","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-14","<p>We announced in January 2018 that £330m from dormant accounts would be distributed to good causes across the UK over the next four years. We are currently working with partners to design the initiatives in such a way that they have a lasting impact for some of the most vulnerable people in the country. We expect to make further announcements shortly about the initial deployment of this funding in England.</p><p> </p><p>Decision making for deploying dormant asset funds in the devolved administrations is fully devolved.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-06-14T14:54:37.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921934/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921934/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921934/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-06-11","Charities: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to his Department's press release, Government unlocking £330 million from dormant accounts to build a fairer society, published on 8 January 2018, how much of the £330 million recovered from dormant accounts has been distributed to charities.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","152189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921935","Department for Education","false","2018-06-19","<p>The government encourages students to have a healthy, balanced diet and adopt healthy life choices through the provision of school funding, legislation and guidance.</p><p> </p><p>The School Food Plan (July 2013), has helped to bring about improvements in the provision of school food. We have since launched the new school food standards in January 2015 and they have been widely welcomed by schools. The standards severely restrict foods that are high in fat, salt and sugar, as well as low quality reformed or reconstituted foods. They ban crisps, confectionery and high-sugar drinks. The standards apply to all food and drink provided to pupils in schools.</p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-06-19T15:42:33.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921935/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921935/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921935/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-11","School Meals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what progress his Department has made on the School Food Plan.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","152093"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921936","Home Office","false","2018-06-14","<p>On 8 March we launched a 12 week public consultation on proposals for a landmark domestic abuse Bill and a supporting package of practical action to transform the response to domestic abuse. The consultation closed on 31 May. Over 3,200 responses to the consultation were received. The responses to the consultation are being considered and a draft Bill will be published later this session.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-06-14T16:22:01.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921936/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921936/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/921936/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-11","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the timetable is for his Department to respond to it's consultation on the draft Domestic Violence and Abuse Bill; and what the timetable is for further steps to be taken in relation to that Bill.","false","Biography information for Martin Whitfield","East Lothian","Martin Whitfield","152267"
